column2: Izak Benbasat is an associate professor in the Faculty of Commerce and Business Administration, University of British Columbia. He received his Ph.D. in Management Information Systems from the University of Minnesota in 1974. His research interests include the investigation of the human-computer interface and the behavioral factors influencing information systems use. He has published articles in these topics in the Communications of the ACM, IEEE Journal of Systems, Man, and Cybernetics and the Journal of Accounting Research, among others.
